  "prompt": "Do anti-money laundering regulations exist?",
  "response": "Yes, anti-money laundering (AML) regulations exist in many countries around the world. These regulations are designed to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income. Key elements typically include:\n\n1. Requiring financial institutions to:\n- Verify customer identities\n- Report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Implement compliance programs\n\n2. Major regulatory frameworks:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- EU Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- International compliance standards\n\n3. Sectors typically covered:\n- Banks\n- Credit unions\n- Investment firms\n- Money transfer services\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Casino and gambling industries\n\nThese regulations aim to detect and prevent financial crimes like money laundering, terrorist financing, and other illegal financial activities.",
